#MEM id=calibration-tracker source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Psychology/Daniel_Kahneman/skills/custom/calibration-tracker/SKILL.md savings=11%
M||tx|---
M||name|calibration-tracker
M||desc|Brier score tracking for kh's prediction accuracy over time. Logs predictions vs actuals, detects drift by domain, recalibrates confidence thresholds. Referenced in principles.md — this is the implementation.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|Confidence ≠ accuracy. This applies to kh as much as to any other ag. A 🔴 verdict issued w/ hi confidence that mc later overrides is a calibration er — not just a disagreement. This skill makes kh's prediction accuracy measurable and improvable over time.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|What|Kahn|
M|What|tx|\| Prediction tp \| Example \| Verifiable when \|
M|What|tx|\|----------------\|---------\|----------------\|
M|What|tx|\| Bias impact \| "This anchoring effect will reduce conversion rate if uncorrected" \| After cg results come in \|
M|What|tx|\| Verdict calibration \| "🔴 block — this loss aversion CTA will damage br trust" \| After Stark reviews and decides \|
M|What|tx|Both tp are logged. Both are scored.
M|What|tx|---
M|Brie|tx|The Brier score measures prediction accuracy for probabilistic forecasts.
M|Brie|**Fo|** `Brier = (fc probability − actual outcome)²`
M|Brie|- Pe|0.00
M|Brie|- Pr|0.25
M|Brie|- Co|> 0.25
M|Brie|**Ho|**
M|Brie|- Wh|"I estimate 70% chance this anchoring effect reduces conversion if uncorrected."
M|Brie|- Wh|fc probability (0.70), actual outcome (1 = happened, 0 = did not happen), Brier score.
M|Brie|it|Track by domain (cp, financial, growth, st) — drift in one domain doesn't necessarily mean drift in others.
M|Brie|tx|---
